post_text:
Paraprofessional
Category: Support Staff/Paraprofessional
Date Posted: 8/26/2020
Location: Goodhue Elementary School
Date of Availability: 08/31/2020
Date Closing: Open until filled

DEPT: Paraprofessional Team
SUPERVISOR: Elementary Principal
START DATE: August 31, 2020
HOURS PER WEEK DURING SCHOOL: approx. 35-40
Salary: TBD per Support Staff Agreement
Qualifications: Two Year Degree
Responsibilities and Duties

-Assist teacher with conducting lessons, managing the classroom and developing materials

-Track student progress during the school year

-May need to work with students of special needs and support our special education teachers

-Empower students through programs designed to enhance their academic, social and emotional development

-Work with computers and other technical resources available to support student learning

-Supervise lunch and recess activities

-Become a Type III driver to support transportation needs of students

-Partake in Professional Development to increase your learning and understanding of student needs and district goals-

post_text:
The Goodhue School is looking for a Full-Time Custodian

Full-time Custodian:
The Goodhue School is seeking a highly motivated individual to take on the responsibilities of a full-time Custodian. Desired qualities for this position include a strong work ethic, current skills- or the willingness to develop skills- in maintenance and cleaning, the ability to work as a positive member of a team, leadership/management skills, and a desire to support the primary mission of the school which is student learning.

Pay is commensurate with licensure (boiler specialist, boiler 1st and/or second class, or chief boiler), experience, and qualifications.

The position is year-round and full time and qualifies for benefits.

If you have any questions in regards to this position, please contact the Head Custodian and Grounds Keeper, Karyn Edelbach, at 651-923-4447 or by email at edelbach@goodhue.k12.mn.us

Apply online: https://www.applitrack.com/sscschools/onlineapp/jobpostings/view.asp?district=37878&all=1

Dear Wildcat Families,

The Minnesota Department of Education is working closely with the Minnesota Department of Health to plan for the 2020-2021 school year, and they want to hear from families about their experience with distance learning.

The feedback is extremely valuable, and the information learned will help as the Department of Education plans for next year.

Please complete the following survey: http://sgiz.mobi/s3/2020-Parent-Distance-Learning-Feedback-Survey

The survey will close on June 30, 2020.

Thanks,
Evan Gough, Superintendent

Dear MS/HS Students and Parents,

Due to the Governor Walz's Stay at Home order:
Tomorrow, Friday, March 27th, Middle and High school students should pick up their locker supplies from 2:00-5:00 pm. Pick up will be behind the school at Door 5. Student belongings will be alphabetized.

Reminders:

*Students and parents will not be allowed in the school

*Use social distancing when picking up supplies

*Locker rooms will be cleaned out at a later date

Distance Learning will begin on Monday, let's make sure you have all your supplies!

Thank you!

Goodhue Public School will be offering lunches to our students while school is not in session. Lunches will be charged to the student’s account at the following prices:
$2.90, grade 7-12
$2.80, grade 4-6
$2.70, grades K-3
F/R for those who qualify

Lunches will be available for pickup from 11:30am - 12:00pm at the following locations:
Bellechester Community Center
Car Wash
Dressen’s Saloon
Featherstone Townhall
Goodhue School - Door #1
Roller Rink, Belle Creek
St. Columbkill Church
St. Peter’s Church, Belvidere

If you wish to purchase a lunch(es) for your child(ren) for the week of March 17-20th please submit your request via the Student Lunch Request Form by 6:00am on Tuesday, March 17, 2020. Please submit one form per child. Families will have the option to submit these requests on a weekly basis while school is not in session.

Sincerely,
Evan Gough, Superintendent
Goodhue Public School

post_text:
Building Project Underway

Exciting work recently started on the Goodhue School project. Soil correction is currently underway for the gym and classroom additions on the east side of the campus. Work on the footings will start once the soil corrections are completed.

A groundbreaking ceremony is planned for Friday, April 17 at 2:30 PM. More information on the location of the ceremony will come out at a later time.

Updates on the building project can be found at the following link on the school district website: http://www.goodhue.k12.mn.us/district/building_project
“Like” Goodhue Public Schools on Facebook for live videos and updates on the project.

Bee Kind Craft Day
This class is a great way to create 3 reminders of the schools' focus on BEEing Kind. We will start by painting a 10” kindness quote wood sign the colors of your choice. While the paint is drying, we will fashion a yellow sequin kindness pillow. After all that crafting the busy kindness bees deserve a treat so we will decorate a bumblebee cupcake to enjoy in class! (This class includes products that may include nuts, gluten, and dairy). Instructor: Renee Reindary
